<Author>Purplemuffin
<Content>Dissapointed! We stayed at ShangriLa Hotel for 4 nights in December 08. We stayed at Tower wings. We have high expectation because of the good reviews. However we find the hotel disappointing due to the following reason.Check in was okay, although the staff at the door seems to be busy talking among themselves and ignore us completely. We were given a room in the end of the corridor next to the emergency stair and storage room. The room is not even in the same hallway with other rooms, but inside a separate small square room with bare wall and terrible light fittings. Definitely doesn鈥檛 feel like 5 star hotel at all.When we first enter the room, the hotel TV Station is broken. Normally in 5 star hotel (even 4 star) the guest will expect some form of greetings and welcome with the guest鈥檚 name on TV. Not in ShangriLa, they don鈥檛 even bother to fix the hotel TV Station for 3 days. Also the light bulb inside the room in the entrance is broken. We notice immediately and notify one of the staff. But it took them 2 days and another phone call to front desk for this simple thing to be rectify. Lack of care and ignorance of the staff. Definitely not 5 star ecperience.The room itself have plenty of space and the bed is comfy. It has a decent size LCD TV. However, the room looks old and the furniture is outdated. The bathroom doesn鈥檛 even looks nice let alone luxurious. The shower is inside the bathtub, which we hate and for famous ShangriLa 5 star hotel, we expect a separate shower. The tile grout in the bath area is disgusting. Inside the room there is a spot in the carpet. Therefore we feel that the cleanliness standard is very low. And not worthy the money you pay for. For the same value better off stay at Mandarin Oriental, see my review.The house keeping forgot to put the face washer on the bathroom and the next day they forgot to put milk for coffee. So we have to ring up to request for basic stuff. The fruit on the plate only consist of 2 old oranges which does not look fresh at all and they don鈥檛 change them for 2 days. There are no orchids or any other flower inside the room. The orchid is actually one per floor, unlike Mandarin Oriental that we stayed previously which have 2 orchids in the room. This little things showed whether the hotel look after and care about the guest or not.The location of the hotel is TERRIBLE. It鈥檚 on Orange Groove Rd, which is located on the far side of Orchard Rd. To walk from the nearest MRT 鈥?Orchard will take at least 20 mins and to walk to Takashimaya will take 25-30 mins. And this walk is outdoor in the humid and hot wheatear. Take note that the walk back to the hotel from Orchard is on the steep hill which leave you breathless, and when it鈥檚 raining you will be soaking wet. Another point, if you feel hungry at night and want to get a drink at night outside the hotel, nothing open within 10 mins walk from the hotel, you have to walk a long way to Orchard Rd. Way too far.The only good thing about ShangriLa is the pool. The pool area is great with 2 separate kiddies pool and refreshing water fountain. The spa for adults is great for relaxation after a long day of walking  shopping. The service is the pool is non existent, you have to request for pool towel yourself and the staff is not very attentive, unlike other hotel that we stayed before where the staff really look after and spoiled the guest very well. 
