<Content>Wow !! Honeymoon hotel We booked the Shangri-La for a 2 night stopover as part of our honeymoon. We decided to arrive on foot carrying our own luggage from the train station on Orchard Road. On our arrival, we quickly realised that this chosen method of arrival was a rarety as we staggered past the Ferraris and Aston Martins parked outside literally dripping in sweat, and gasping for a breath of the ice cold air conditioned air beyond the doors. We were just speechless on our arrival, due to the cavenous proportions of the main reception which exhudes grandeur to the finest degree.We were swiftly rescued by a delightful member of reception staff, who looked at us in utter amazement for choosing to walk there! She promptly ordered someone to relieve us of our bags, and within minutes, we were promptly checked in and escorted to our room in the Garden Wing. The hotel had taken it upon themselves to upgrade us free of charge to a Garden Room which boasted a huge double balcony which was 3 times the size of the room itself. We even had a Chocolate Wedding Cake waiting for us on our arrival, with a personal message iced on the top! Our room overlooked the pool at the very far end of the Garden Wing in a really private  quiet part of the hotel. Our room was beautiful, clean and fresh with the biggest and most comfortable bed we have ever slept in. We opted for the extra of breakfast at The Line each morning, which is a huge extravagance, but really really shouldn't be missed. I have nothing but praise for every aspect of this hotel - we were made to feel like royalty on every occasion that we came into contact with staff. The pool was amazing, as was The Spa, and a drink on the top floor Bar is a 'must do warm-up' to anyones evening in town. If I really had to scratch around for a negative point, then all I can say is that the water in our shower didn't drain away as quick as I would have liked - but that is being really picky. Such a shame that we couldn't have stayed there longer as there is just so much more to see and do at the hotel with numerous restaurants shops and services on offer. We would definately LOVE to have the opportunity to go back there one day .......... 
