<Content>Absolute Class! This was our second visit to Singapore and although we thoroughly enjoyed our stay at the Oriental the first time round, we wanted a change of scenery. We'd read good things about the Shangri-La and this was our third stay in a SL hotel so we had a high level of expectation. Without any hesitation, I can say that this hotel was fantastic, easily the best Shangri-La we've been to and the best 5 star city hotel we've stayed at in the Far East.We were welcomed by a number of staff on arrival and whisked over to the Garden Wing. We were taken straight to our room where check-in took place and our bags were delivered. Shortly afterwards, complimentary tea and fruit was brought to our room. Everything was done efficiently and professionally - ideal after a long flight. We didn't feel like we were in a large city hotel and the staff deserve credit for this from the way they welcomed us and the check-in process.The room was large and nicely decorated with a large veranda (we had a corner room). The bed was huge and very comfortable. The mini-bar was expensive though. The Garden wing has a resort ambiance with outdoor covered walkways, a central garden, pond and waterfall. It has good access to the pool. The pool is quite large and the area around is really pretty. My only criticism is that on the weekends, it was difficult to get a sun lounger and perhaps more are needed during busy times. On weekdays, it was much quieter.We only ate in The Line which is an amazing buffet with a wide range of cuisines. Make sure you are hungry to take full advantage of them and to especially make the most of the chocolate fountain! Breakfast is equally as good with a good range of fruit juices, lassi, eggs however you want them, asian food, fresh waffles and pancakes with fresh honey and much more!We had one drink in the Blu bar, which was expensive but on the top floor so you get a different view of the city. We did receive a voucher towards the drinks by filling in a guest review form so it worked out at a reasonable price for us.We took taxis to most places which are cheap and we walked down to the Orchard Road on some occasions. It takes around 5-10 minutes.In general, the service was of a high standard and consistent, the food was excellent as were the rooms. The pool was really good for both swimming and relaxing too. I will be returning to Singapore if only to stay in the Shangri-La. And for the chocolate fountain of course! 
