<Content>quality service makes the difference In January 2005, I had two short stays in this place that I would describe as close to heaven on earth. Both stays were in the Tower wing on the club floors, giving you not only an excellent view (the view on the 24th breakfast floor is superb) but also spacious quality rooms and great support from the club floor team. The Shangri-La delivers great opprtunities for relaxation while located close to busy Orchard Road. Once you have staid here, you will -as a business traveller- not loose time anymore while planning your next visit to Singapore; you'll just book the Shangri-La again, and again and again. The only comment I would have -recognising that some might have a different opinion on this- is that the Club lounge is fully non-smoking; there is plenty of room to organise a corner for people who enjoy smoking. And for the late evening hours don't forget : go to the Blue bar again and again and again. 
